{"name": "nuts-calkit", "metadata": {"name": "NUTS-calkit", "version": "0.0.5", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Non-Uniform Temperature Steel beam Calculation toolKit", "upload_time": 1733796585}, "documentation": ["# Manuscript of NUTS_calkit\n**Non-Uniform Temperature Steel beam Calculation toolKit**  \n_Yang. Li, Yong. Wang et al. May 2024, The University of Manchester_\n\n## 1. Python commands:\n\n### 1.1 Creating Beam Object\n### Access\n*from NUTS_cakit import NUTS_cakit as nc*\n*nc.Beam()*\n\n**<<<<< Required arguments >>>>>**  \nd:  Section depth  \nw:  Section width  \nft: Flange thickness  \nwt: Web thickness  \nfpl: Plastic strength of beam  \nE: Elastic modulus  \nG: Shear modulus  \nL: Length  \nt_dist: Temperature distribtuion in the section  \n    Dataformat: [temperature, ratio of the distance from beam top/section depth], 20C <= temperature <= 1200C.  \n    Example: [[600,0],[270,0.7],[100,1]]  \n\n**<<<<< Returning objects >>>>>**  \nBeam object\n \n*b1=nc.Beam(E=210000,G=80770,L=5000,fpl=320,d=320,w=140,ft=10,wt=5,t_dist=[[600, 0], [500, 1]])*\n\n### 1.1.1 Mpl()\n -Beam plastic bending moment\n\n**<<<<< Required arguments >>>>>**  \n -Beam: A NUTS_calkit beam objects\n\n  -*nc.Beam.Mpl()*\n\n### 1.1.2 Mcr()\n -Beam Elastic Critical Bending Moment\n\n**<<<<< Required arguments >>>>>**  \n -Beam: A NUTS_calkit beam objects\n\n  -*nc.Beam.Mcr()*\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "NUTS_calkit", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "NUTS_calkit.main_program", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "NUTS_calkit.main_program.case", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "NUTS_calkit.main_program.a", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "NUTS